This paper deals with privacy concerns related to usage-based automotive insurance programs, which involves monitoring driving behavior using devices installed in vehicles. The paper discusses how speed data collected by these devices can be used to track a person's driving routes and destinations, which raises privacy concerns. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Other likely sub-categories include cs.CY (Computers and Society), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.DB (Databases), and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
